# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  WHITELIST .gitignore
#  Your working folder is ~1.2 GB (etf_yield_calculator, UW Data,
#  dark-pool-dashboard, PDFs, logs, ...). We do NOT want that on GitHub.
#
#  Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING, then re-include only the files that make
#  up the online dashboard (~8 MB). To publish another project later,
#  add a matching `!/<folder>/` line below.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1. Ignore everything at the repo root
/*

# 2. Re-include the deployment machinery
!/.gitignore
!/.nojekyll
!/.github/
!/index.html
!/dashboard.html
!/DEPLOY.md

# 3. Re-include the dashboards wired into the combined view
!/52weeknewhigh/
!/barchart100/
!/mostactive/
!/topgainers1m/
!/topoptions/
!/overallpicks/

# 4. Inside those folders, drop noise we don't want online
**/.claude/
**/logs/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.DS_Store
**/.ipynb_checkpoints/
